In 1982, a public artist named Agnes Denes planted a 1.8 acre wheat field on a chunk of land in New York City. Commissioned by the Public Art Fund, Denes cultivated the wheat to grow a message regarding economic inequity in the world after the project concluded in august, the harvested wheat was sent to countries in need.
